                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                A work in Persian on different topics within the fileds of poetics and rhetoric. There are several works available from this author, including <title>Nayl al-Marām fī Maẕhab al-Aʾimmah</title> and <title>Naẓm al-Bayān</title>.
                                This work, however, is not attributed to him in any of the available catalogues. The current copy is comprised of an introduction and several 'merits'. The first Merit is on Mutamassikāt and the last on ʾUyūb-i Qāfīyah.
                            </summary>
                        <msItem>
                            <locus from="30a" to="33a">ff. 30a-33a</locus>
                            <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                            <note type="content-genre">Rhetoric</note>
                            <author key="person_f6413">
                                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Rāzī, ʿAbd al-Raḥīm ibn Maʿrūf, -after 839 AH/1436‏</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="per" type="standard">رازی، عبدالرحیم بن معروف، -بعد از ۸۳۹ق/۱۴۳۶</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21314">[Taʿmīm-i Shuʿarāʾ]</title>
                            <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21314">[تعمیم شعراء]</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="per">
                                بسمله، کتاب در تعمیم شعرا از گفتار عبدالرحیم بن معروف. بدانکه تعریض بضاد معجمه و خواه بضاء معجمه در لغة مدح گفتن است…
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="per">
                                … تکرار قافیه در اشعار دلیل عدم سلامت طبع شاعر و عدم ممارست اوست بر الفاظ و تکرار قافیه را پسند ندارند.
                            </explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="ara">
                                تمّ و کمّل الحمد لله حق حمده.
                            </colophon>
                            <listBibl>
                                <head>Sequence Number in the Persian Catalogue:</head>
                                <bibl><choice><abbr>FAW</abbr><expan>Ferdowsi Library, Wadham College, University of Oxford - Minasian Collection</expan></choice> 193</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <listBibl>
                                <head>On the Web:</head>
                                <bibl type="digitised-version">
                                    <ref target="https://dlib.ical.ir/faces/search/bibliographic/biblioFullView.jspx?_afPfm=vn725ad3v">Digitized version of another copy of this work.</ref>
                                    <note>The only work by this author in the field of rhetoric is this one retained at the Library, Museum and Documentation Center of the Islamic Consultative Assembly;
                                        ff. 149 and 150 of that copy seem to be the Arabic version of our copy.</note>
                                </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <note>No sign was found of this work in any of the available catalogues.</note>
                        </msItem>
